  <details>
    <summary>Why this keeps happening</summary>
    <p>Most of these are EXACT match keywords that should never have made it through harvesting if anyone was watching. <em>"fernsehsessel"</em> and <em>"fernsehsessel elektrisch verstellbar"</em> are the same product category burning €270 combined — probably the "Relaxsessel Keyword" campaign bidding broadly into terms the actual product doesn't convert on. A weekly negation review on terms with 50+ clicks and 0 orders would catch all of these in 30 minutes per week. That's the cheapest line item in any PPC service contract.</p>
  </details>

