  <h2>Four mega-campaigns holding the account together <span class="window-tag w30">30d</span></h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Campaign</th><th class="num">Ad Groups</th><th class="num">ASINs in worst group</th><th class="num">Spend</th><th class="num">Sales</th><th class="num">ROAS</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><strong>A15</strong></td><td class="num">12</td><td class="num bad">535</td><td class="num">€1,296</td><td class="num">€17,207</td><td class="num good">13.27x</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>A20</strong></td><td class="num">12</td><td class="num bad">192</td><td class="num">€866</td><td class="num">€11,062</td><td class="num good">12.78x</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>A07</strong></td><td class="num">12</td><td class="num">54</td><td class="num">€99</td><td class="num">€3,463</td><td class="num good">35.08x</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>A10</strong></td><td class="num">12</td><td class="num bad">406</td><td class="num">€372</td><td class="num">€2,254</td><td class="num">6.05x</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>A04</strong></td><td class="num">9</td><td class="num">16</td><td class="num">€14</td><td class="num">€706</td><td class="num good">49.79x</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>These five campaigns do a lot of heavy lifting. A15 alone generates €17K in 30 days. They're profitable — that's not the problem. The problem is visibility and control:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>535 ASINs in a single ad group</strong> (A15-K30) means per-ASIN bid optimization is impossible. One bid covers 535 products at different prices, margins, and competitive positions.</li>
    <li><strong>No per-product copy</strong> because ad copy is attached to the product listing, but grouped management means winners and losers get the same budget treatment.</li>
    <li><strong>Negative keyword hygiene is broken</strong>. Negating a term inside a 535-ASIN ad group risks killing a converter that happens to match on a different ASIN.</li>
    <li><strong>Harvesting is manual and slow</strong>. When these campaigns discover a winning search term, promoting it to a proper exact-match campaign requires finding which of 535 ASINs it belongs to.</li>
  </ul>

