  <h4>Recommended structure per product</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Auto Catch-all</strong> — discovery at low bids, harvest source</li>
    <li><strong>Manual Exact</strong> — proven converters, scaled aggressively</li>
    <li><strong>Manual Broad / Phrase</strong> — mid-funnel exploration</li>
    <li><strong>PAT Competitor</strong> — targets top competitor ASINs (formalizing what auto campaigns already discover)</li>
    <li><strong>Brand Defense</strong> — protects own keyword space</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Splitting the five mega-campaigns into per-ASIN campaigns would add 200–300 new campaigns. Sounds painful, but most professionally managed catalogs of this size run 500–1,500 active campaigns.</p>

