  <h2>Sponsored Display is practically absent <span class="window-tag w30">30d</span></h2>

  <div class="card rose">
    <h4>The numbers</h4>
    <p><strong>€970 total SD spend over the last 30 days</strong> across 18 campaigns (13 active). Combined SD sales: €3,515. For context: this is an account generating €1.14M in 60-day revenue, with 2,040 ASINs producing sales and an obvious opportunity in every category where shoppers compare 5–10 products before buying. SD should represent 15–25% of total PPC spend — here it's 4%.</p>
  </div>

  <p>Beyond the volume gap, the SD setup itself shows that nobody is actively managing it. Of 18 campaigns, most are named generically ("Garten Display", "SD_Pergolen_PAT_...") and several are paused with zero activity. There's no systematic view-remarketing, no competitor ASIN defensive layer, no category-based audience targeting.</p>

