  <p>Competitor ASIN matching is producing disproportionate sales at a ROAS substantially above account average — and it's happening <em>by accident</em> through Auto targeting. Every other category of PPC activity would get more attention if anyone knew how much revenue came from this specific mechanic.</p>

  <details>
    <summary>The play</summary>
    <p>Pull the top 50 competitor ASINs by 64d sales attribution. Build dedicated PAT campaigns per top-revenue product against those ASINs with deliberate bids. Use "Targeting Expansion" in PAT to pick up lookalike competitor listings. Shift part of the Auto-campaign budget into these PAT campaigns once they prove out.</p>
    <p>The risk is minimal because the data proves the demand. The payoff is structural — turning a happy accident into a system means it can be scaled, optimized, and measured properly.</p>
