  <p>Without concentrated TOS pressure on target keywords for 2–4 weeks per new listing, products either rank organically by accident or never rank at all. If even 5% of these invisible ASINs could be recovered through ranking PPC, that's 269 additional products contributing to topline.</p>

  <p>The question Helium 10 data would answer definitively: what are the top keywords for those invisible ASINs and where are they ranking organically? Without that data we can only note the gap. The hypothesis is straightforward: in competitive categories like Garten and Haushalt, organic ranking without PPC pressure is rare.</p>

